FBIS4-9841 "drlat064_g_94017" FBIS-LAT-94-064 Daily Report 2 Apr 1994 Guatemala U.S. Citizen Sustains Irreversible Brain Damage U.S. Citizen Sustains Irreversible Brain Damage PA0204025194 Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas in Spanish 0137 GMT 2 Apr 94 PA0204025194 Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas Spanish BFN [Report by Diego Andres de Gatica] [Text] U.S. citizen (June Diane Tomarweeks), 54, has irreversible brain damage. She is in the intensive care ward of Herrera Llerandi Hospital, Guatemala City. The medical report states her condition has stabilized, but she will have to remain in intensive care. Physicians have reported they had planned to send her to the United States, but the trip will have to wait at least four or five days. A mob that confused her with a child kidnapper attacked the U.S. citizen in San Cristobal Alta Verapaz. The hospital information indicates her condition has stabilized but that the damage to her brain is irreversible.
